I may be an exception, but I only play the 9x9 grids and use the pencil marks (maybe mode) often.  Therefore, I was hoping for upgrades such as:  1.  The keypad needs to be in the old 3x3 layout.  Not only does it put all the buttons in a smaller, more efficient layout, but that arrangement also mimics the layout of the maybes in the playing grid making it more intuitive.  2. I would also like to see an option for 2 colors of pencil marks.  There are situations where you may have, for example, 6 maybes in each square of a given cage, but you may know that that cage has to contain one or two of those numbers.  I would like to be able to distinguish those two cases with different colors.  3.  In addition, when in maybe mode, I would like the colors of the numbers in the keypad to change to reflect the numbers entered into the selected square. as detailed in item 2 above.  That way the status of that square could be seen without having to look back and forth between the number pad and the playing gird.  4.  Add a button to completely fill a square with all 9 maybes in one click.

The layout of the buttons is not great. If it was not for a quick reintroduction of the digit buttons, this would not have passed quality control. For the current state of the input mode you can also look at the dot above the grid (blue for normal mode, orange for maybe). Also the digits on the buttons are displayed in yellow in maybe mode.
